German Banks Could Bear Another Greek Writedown, BDB Group Says

-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t   a n d   F r a n c i n e   L a c q u a
-- 
2011-09-29T08:54:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/german-banks-could-bear-another-greek-writedown-bdb-group-says.html
German banks could withstand
another writedown of Greek sovereign debt and are prepared “for
every kind of haircut that comes up” in a European effort to
contain the spread of contagion in the euro region,  Michael Kemmer , the general manager of the BdB Association of German
Banks, said in a Bloomberg Television interview today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicholas Comfort in Frankfurt at 
